<li id="cite_note-89"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-89">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFMorn1982" class="citation book">Morn (1982). <i>The Eye That Never Sleeps</i>. p.&#160;99. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-253-32086-0" title="Special:BookSources/0-253-32086-0"><bdi>0-253-32086-0</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Eye+That+Never+Sleeps&amp;rft.pages=99&amp;rft.date=1982&amp;rft.isbn=0-253-32086-0&amp;rft.au=Morn&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHaymarket+affair" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/> On April 9, 1885, Pinkertons shot and killed an elderly man at the McCormick Harvester Company Works in Chicago. On October 19, 1886, they shot and killed a man in Chicago's packinghouse district. <a href="/wiki/Labor_spies#A_historical_overview" class="mw-redirect" title="Labor spies">More info</a>.</span>
